## Limitations

The data on late-term abortions is limited by inconsistent reporting across states and the lack of a federal mandate for comprehensive data collection. Additionally, the term "late-term" is not consistently defined across studies and reports, which can lead to variations in data interpretation. Furthermore, the sensitive nature of the topic means that data may be influenced by political and social biases.